asis for the Trinity, which was established as part of Christian dogma in 325 CE (at the Council of Nicea).  I not only have never read the Bible all the way through, but I was raised Congregationalist which apparently doesn't think much of the Trinity since (despite years of Sunday school) I never heard the term used until a Protestant Traditions class in college.  Can those more enlightened than I make the argument for and against the Trinity?  (And apologies if this has already been discussed).  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
